<TITLE> Wazed Miah writes to CA for Hasina's treatment in US: aide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 4 (bdnews24.com)  Former prime minister Sheikh Hasina's husband MA Wazed Miah wrote a letter to chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Tuesday with an appeal to send his wife to the US for medical treatment, an aide said. Hasina's special assistant Dr Hasan Mahmud told bdnews24.com that he had gone to the Chief Adviser's Office, along with her nephew barrister Fazle Noor Tapash, and handed the letter at 8.20pm. Hasan Mahmud said: "In the letter Dr Wazed Miah mentioned different health complications of Sheikh Hasina." In the letter, Wazed Miah said Hasina had earlier received ear treatment in the US. "So her treatment is not possible elsewhere," Hasan Mahmud said, referring to the letter. Wazed Miah urged the government to immediately release Hasina and arrange her proper treatment in the US, the aide said. bdnews24.c
